<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge" />
    <meta name="Description" content="Enter your description here" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/twitter-bootstrap/4.6.0/css/bootstrap.min.css"/>
    <link
     
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.3/css/all.min.css"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/style.css" />
    <title>KWK Tech</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="bg">
        <img src="/images/kt_bg.png" alt="Background Image" />
      </div>
      <div class="head">
        <div class="logo">
          <img src="/images/kt_logo.png" alt="Logo" />
        </div>
        <div class="btn">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="myBtn"
            data-toggle="modal"
            data-target="#myModal"
          >
            Investors
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="emblem">
        <img src="/images/kt.png" alt="Emblem" />
      </div>
      <div class="heading">
        <h1>is for KWK Tech</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="text">
        <p>
          KwK Tech has a similar approach to other stand-out tech companies,
          which is why we are not a conventional company. We strive to push the
          envelope. “Impossible” or “can’t” is not an acceptable answer or
          conclusion. It is frustrating trying to partner with companies that
          are rooted in saying “SORRY we can’t do that”.
          <span onclick="myFunction()" id="more">See More</span>
        </p>
        <span id="more_text">
          <p>
            KwK Tech is focused on making results, not excuses. We pride
            ourselves on thinking outside the box. I spent over 30 years
            designing and engineering magic illusions for magicians to make the
            impossible possible. Impossible was never a conclusion, thinking
